'''Kunos Simulazioni s.r.l.''' is an Italian software development studio that specializes in creating driving simulations. The company is headquartered at the [[ACI Vallelunga Circuit]] near Rome and was established in 2005 with the goal of developing software for varying needs from solutions for professional racing teams to consumer software.<ref name="Kunos_interview" /><ref name="kunos_web">{{Cite web |url=http://www.kunos-simulazioni.com/main/ |title=Kunos Simulazioni Website|publisher=Kunos Simulazioni |accessdate=28 May 2014}}</ref>

The studio's latest major title, ''[[Assetto Corsa]]'', was released on 19 December 2014 on Microsoft Windows and received critical acclaim upon its release.<ref name="steam_ac-release">{{cite web|title=Assetto Corsa V1.0 is now OUT!|url=https://steamcommunity.com/games/assettocorsa/announcements/detail/141066961014018953|publisher=[[Steam (software)|Steam]]|accessdate=26 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Assetto Corsa Steam reviews|url=http://store.steampowered.com/app/244210/#app_reviews_hash|website=Steam|publisher=Valve|accessdate=2 May 2016}}</ref> A console version of ''Assetto Corsa'' for [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]] in partnership with publisher [[505 Games]] was announced in June 2015 and was released in August 2016.<ref name="console_announcement">{{cite web|title=Assetto Corsa Console Announcement|url=http://www.assettocorsa.net/coming-to-console-2016/|publisher=Kunos Simulazioni | accessdate=25 May 2016}}</ref>

The company was purchased by 505's parent company Digital Bros S.p.A. in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSFWN1FA0IA|title=BRIEF-Digital Bros signs prelim. agreement to buy 100 pct Kunos Simulazioni|date=20 January 2017|publisher=|via=Reuters}}</ref>

In February 2018 the company announced ''[[Assetto Corsa Competizione]]'', a new title with the official [[Blancpain GT Series]] licence, which released on 12 September 2018 in the [[Steam (software)|Steam]] Early Access program.<ref name="ACC-website">{{Cite web |url=https://www.assettocorsa.net/competizione/ |title=Assetto Corsa Competizione |publisher=Kunos Simulazioni |accessdate=21 February 2018}}</ref><ref name="Blancpain-Announcement">{{Cite web |url=https://www.blancpain-gt-series.com/news/1173/blancpain-gt-series-announces-move-into-sim-racing-with-assetto-corsa-competizione |title=Blancpain GT Series announces move into sim racing with Assetto Corsa Competizione |publisher=[[Stéphane Ratel Organisation]] |accessdate=21 February 2018}}</ref> It was released on 29 May 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.blancpain-gt-series.com/news/1527/assetto-corsa-competizione-confirmed-for-official-public-release-on-29-may- |website=blancpain-gt-series.com |publisher=[[Stéphane Ratel Organisation]] |title=Assetto Corsa Competizione confirmed for official public release on 29 May |accessdate=2019-04-18}}</ref>

